### E-commerce API Requests
### Use with "REST Client" extension in VS Code

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api

### 1. Get All Products
GET {{baseUrl}}/products

###

### 2. Get Product By ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/products/1

###

### 3. Add New Product
POST {{baseUrl}}/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Ultra Slim Laptop",
    "price": 999.00,
    "category": "electronics",
    "description": "Powerful and portable laptop for professionals.",
    "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1496181133206-80ce9b88a853?w=500&q=80"
}

###

### 4. Update Product
PUT {{baseUrl}}/products/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Premium Wireless Headphones (Updated)",
    "price": 219.99,
    "category": "electronics",
    "description": "Now with even better noise cancellation and battery life.",
    "image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1505740420928-5e560c06d30e?w=500&q=80"
}

###

### 5. Login (To get Token if needed for protected routes)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "somu@gmail.com",
    "password": "root123"
}
